    <div class="main-page-wrapper variable-size">
        <h1 class="question">Do I need a gun/license to attend an event?</h1>
        <div>
            <p class="answer">
                Not at all! We provide the guns and supervision, you provide the smiles.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="main-page-wrapper variable-size">
        <h1 class="question">What gear do I need?</h1>
        <div>
            <p class="answer">
                If you are only planning on attending an event, you probably only need to bring some water, food, money,
                and a smile!
                Eye and ear protection are always mandatory when operating a firearm, and so typically we can provide
                the ear protection,
                but it will be on you to bring some eye protection (like sunglasses).
                <br><br>
                If you're interested in joining the team, you're going to, at the very least need your <a href="https://www.rcmp-grc.gc.ca/en/firearms/licensing">PAL</a>.
                Teammates can provide a shotgun if needed, but it is always recommended to buy your own.
                You'll also want a belt and a <a href="https://www.cabelas.ca/product/96085/allen-eliminator-single-box-shell-carrier">shotshell carrier</a> (most of the team uses one of these).
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="main-page-wrapper variable-size">
        <h1 class="question">What am I looking for in a shotgun?</h1>
        <div>
            <p class="answer">
                <b>Gauge:</b> 12 or 20ga
                <br>
                <b>Action:</b> Over-under or semi
                <br>
                <b>Chokes (ideal to less so):</b> Skeet, Improved Cylinder, Cylinder, Modified
                <br>
                <b>Barrel length:</b> > 26in (28-30 is usually the sweet spot)
                <br>
                <b>Recommendations ($-$$$):</b> Remington 1100, Browning/Beretta Semi, Browning Citori, Beretta Silver Pigeon
                <br>
                We always recommend that you <b>try before you buy!</b>
                <br>
                <b>Where to buy:</b> I always recommend buying used from either <a href="https://www.canadiangunnutz.com/">CGN</a> or <a href="https://www.gunpost.ca/">GunPost</a>.
                <br>
                Buying new? Buy local! <b>GunCo</b>, Stittsville Range, Sports Action, and Cabelas
                <br>
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

